00:19:05,395 --> 00:19:07,021
By the way, are you sure?

262
00:19:07,564 --> 00:19:08,773
They're seeing each other?

263
00:19:08,857 --> 00:19:10,817
But they barely talk to each other.

264
00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:13,027
That's just a cover.

265
00:19:13,778 --> 00:19:16,281
They suddenly became awkward,
not even saying hi.

266
00:19:16,364 --> 00:19:18,116
That's more suspicious.

267
00:19:18,199 --> 00:19:20,827
Yeah, I showed you the note.

268
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:21,995
"With love."

269
00:19:22,078 --> 00:19:24,247
They even have pet names for each other.

270
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:25,623
They watched a movie alone.

271
00:19:28,042 --> 00:19:29,752
Hello, thanks for calling
Jinlee Publishing.

272
00:19:29,836 --> 00:19:34,132
Right, Chun-woo said
he saw them having coffee alone that day.

273
00:19:34,215 --> 00:19:35,383
I'm not surprised.

274
00:19:35,466 --> 00:19:37,343
She got hired through connections.

275
00:19:37,427 --> 00:19:40,013
They had coffee and lunch alone.

276
00:19:40,096 --> 00:19:41,723
It was obvious.

277
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:43,141
Thank you.

278
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,779
-U-ri.
-Yes?

279
00:19:56,863 --> 00:20:00,074
-Are you going to Sang-jin's office?
-Yes, do you need anything?

280
00:20:01,117 --> 00:20:02,368
No, never mind.

281
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:09,876
Did you hear that?

282
00:20:18,927 --> 00:20:20,595
The designer called

283
00:20:21,012 --> 00:20:24,724
and wanted your confirmation
on the revised draft

284
00:20:25,308 --> 00:20:29,562
and wanted you to send
emails to this address.

285
00:20:30,313 --> 00:20:33,024
-Okay, thank you.
-Sure.

286
00:20:49,499 --> 00:20:50,833
Sang-jin.

287
00:20:52,085 --> 00:20:53,336
Hey.

288
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:58,132
You didn't hear the broadcast
since you were outside, right?

289
00:20:58,216 --> 00:21:01,803
I was worried about hate comments.
But the reactions are great.

290
00:21:01,886 --> 00:21:04,973
Now, we don't need to worry
about publicity.

291
00:21:05,473 --> 00:21:08,184
That Deborah. "Deborah, breakup icon."

292
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:10,895
She straight up went head-on into it.

293
00:21:10,979 --> 00:21:12,146
She's good.

294
00:21:12,230 --> 00:21:13,940
That's great.

295
00:21:16,025 --> 00:21:17,443
You know what's more amazing?

296
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:22,031
I've got quite a hunch
in the dating department.

297
00:21:22,824 --> 00:21:24,993
I'm quite extraordinary.

298
00:21:26,327 --> 00:21:29,330
She had a live phone call
with a listener who's called 6958.

299
00:21:29,414 --> 00:21:33,167
From the story, I came to think
that there was something going on here.

300
00:21:33,543 --> 00:21:34,919
So I looked it up.

301
00:21:36,379 --> 00:21:38,756
The last digits of
Deborah's phone number is also 6958.

302
00:21:39,882 --> 00:21:42,260
Deborah's ex-boyfriend
wants to get back together.

303
00:21:42,343 --> 00:21:44,470
He said that on a live radio show.

304
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:47,515
If this goes well,

305
00:21:47,598 --> 00:21:50,309
it's perfect for book publicity later.

306
00:21:50,393 --> 00:21:52,979
Perfect storytelling marketing.

307
00:21:53,938 --> 00:21:55,314
That's just an assumption.

308
00:21:55,398 --> 00:21:57,775
And if he confesses his love,
is it guaranteed to work?

309
00:21:57,859 --> 00:22:00,069
It wasn't just a confession of love.

310
00:22:00,528 --> 00:22:03,573
A wholehearted confession
of a man who has surrendered to love.

311
00:22:03,656 --> 00:22:05,825
It was almost like a drama.

312
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,953
The male lead regrets,
comes to his senses,

313
00:22:09,037 --> 00:22:11,372
confesses his love on a live show
and they get back together.

314
00:22:11,748 --> 00:22:13,166
It's so romantic.

315
00:22:13,249 --> 00:22:14,959
What kind of woman
wouldn't be swayed by that?

316
00:22:15,043 --> 00:22:17,211
It even made my heart flutter.

317
00:22:18,254 --> 00:22:20,048
So when is your meeting with Deborah?

318
00:22:20,131 --> 00:22:21,132
What?

319
00:22:21,966 --> 00:22:23,885
Oh, tomorrow.

320
00:22:24,302 --> 00:22:25,303
Tomorrow.

321
00:22:25,386 --> 00:22:27,305
Then we'll find out everything tomorrow.

322
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:32,268
Get a bouquet of flowers tomorrow
before the meeting.

323
00:22:32,602 --> 00:22:35,521
I should have sent one
on behalf of the company.

324
00:22:35,605 --> 00:22:37,857
I was so swamped that it slipped my mind.

325
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:38,983
Come on, man.

326
00:22:39,067 --> 00:22:41,611
When I'm busy,
you should have sent her one already.

327
00:22:41,694 --> 00:22:42,737
You're so clueless...

328
00:22:42,820 --> 00:22:44,947
What did I do wrong?

329
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:46,949
We can give her one tomorrow.

330
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:18,064
Not even a call.

331
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:38,417
-Yes.
-Did you get home all right?

332
00:23:38,501 --> 00:23:39,877
You must be tired.

333
00:23:40,962 --> 00:23:43,714
Why don't we have lunch tomorrow?

334
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:46,759
As friends. Lunch wouldn't hurt.

335
00:23:46,843 --> 00:23:49,262
I'm afraid I can't. I have work.

336
00:23:51,931 --> 00:23:54,725
You're making an excuse
to reject me, aren't you?

337
00:23:55,393 --> 00:23:58,187
I'm not used to this, so I'm confused.

338
00:23:59,772 --> 00:24:01,399
I am rejecting your offer,

339
00:24:01,482 --> 00:24:02,650
but I really have work.

340
00:24:03,317 --> 00:24:05,444
All right, then let's have
dinner together.

341
00:24:05,528 --> 00:24:07,780
If you're going to reject this too,
do it in person.

342
00:24:08,322 --> 00:24:09,365
Bye.

343
00:24:31,387 --> 00:24:33,181
Excuse me.

344
00:24:33,264 --> 00:24:35,349
-I'd like to order.
-Bo-ra.

345
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:37,894
Have French toast
with strawberries on top.

346
00:24:37,977 --> 00:24:40,396
Get another one for me along with yours.

347
00:24:40,479 --> 00:24:42,815
Get another one for me, too.

348
00:24:43,357 --> 00:24:44,400
Get them one.

349
00:24:44,817 --> 00:24:48,446
Look at the way you do business here.

350
00:24:49,071 --> 00:24:50,698
Fine, you two can enjoy that.

351
00:24:50,781 --> 00:24:53,492
And I'll have two Americanos, please.

352
00:24:54,702 --> 00:24:55,703
Why two?

353
00:24:55,786 --> 00:24:56,954
You have company today?

354
00:25:05,838 --> 00:25:07,423
-Hello.
-Hi.

355
00:25:16,307 --> 00:25:20,102
Did you listen to the broadcast yesterday?
I guess you couldn't because of work.

356
00:25:21,103 --> 00:25:22,772
It would have been nice if you did.

357
00:25:24,649 --> 00:25:25,900
I did.

358
00:25:28,236 --> 00:25:29,862
You thanked someone.

359
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:31,864
It was touching.

360
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:37,787
If it was touching, you should have
let me know that you'd heard it.

361
00:25:38,412 --> 00:25:39,705
I waited.

362
00:25:47,129 --> 00:25:50,675
Then did you hear that part, too?
The live phone call?

363
00:25:53,678 --> 00:25:54,845
Yes.

364
00:25:58,557 --> 00:26:02,478
So did you talk with him?

365
00:26:03,646 --> 00:26:06,857
He came to the broadcasting station,
so we briefly talked.

366
00:26:07,817 --> 00:26:08,859
So...

367
00:26:09,944 --> 00:26:12,571
I talked with him all right.

368
00:26:31,257 --> 00:26:32,258
Welcome...

369
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:34,802
Bo-mi.

370
00:26:34,885 --> 00:26:36,762
I heard you work here.

371
00:26:37,346 --> 00:26:39,473
How have you been? It's been a while.

372
00:26:40,266 --> 00:26:41,267
-What's up?
-Hey.

373
00:26:42,643 --> 00:26:43,811
Come on.

374
00:26:43,894 --> 00:26:45,813
You won't even talk to me?

375
00:26:45,896 --> 00:26:47,398
You've become more beautiful, Bo-mi.

376
00:26:49,233 --> 00:26:51,027
Why didn't you call me?

377
00:26:52,445 --> 00:26:53,654
I missed you.

378
00:26:53,738 --> 00:26:56,866
You've become prettier
since I saw you last.

379
00:26:56,949 --> 00:26:58,075
How can you be so pretty?

380
00:26:58,159 --> 00:26:59,618
Gifts from my ex-boyfriend.

381
00:26:59,702 --> 00:27:01,787
Selling at a real bargain.

382
00:27:02,371 --> 00:27:05,374
You said you're selling this
at a bargain after a breakup.

383
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:09,920
Come on, say something to me.

384
00:27:10,004 --> 00:27:13,007
I can't stand this pathetic bullshit.

385
00:27:13,090 --> 00:27:15,426
If you broke up, that's it.
Being desperate and clingy.

386
00:27:15,509 --> 00:27:16,886
Shame on you!

387
00:27:16,969 --> 00:27:18,095
What's the matter?

388
00:27:23,684 --> 00:27:25,144
You'd better give up.

389
00:27:25,227 --> 00:27:27,980
It's too late.
Nothing's going to change anyway.

390
00:27:28,939 --> 00:27:32,026
Who are you, and why are you saying this?

391
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:35,613
Forget it. Stop. It's okay.

392
00:27:36,155 --> 00:27:37,281
Don't you get it?

393
00:27:37,948 --> 00:27:39,533
I'm the current boyfriend

394
00:27:39,617 --> 00:27:41,994
of your ex-girlfriend
whom you can't possibly get over!

395
00:27:56,384 --> 00:27:58,469
No way. You must be joking.

396
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:02,723
No, Jin-ho. Don't.

397
00:28:02,807 --> 00:28:04,475
That's not it. Okay?

398
00:28:06,227 --> 00:28:07,395
Jealous much?

399
00:28:07,478 --> 00:28:11,565
Bo-mi is perfectly happy with me.
So can you just get lost?

400
00:28:11,649 --> 00:28:13,776
Stop it.

401
00:28:14,610 --> 00:28:17,029
He's my sister's ex-boyfriend.

402
00:28:18,906 --> 00:28:19,907
What?

403
00:28:34,630 --> 00:28:37,216
All right, seems like
it's time to be upfront about it.

404
00:28:38,092 --> 00:28:40,886
I know you're all wondering
what is happening.

405
00:28:41,679 --> 00:28:42,763
Here's the thing.

406
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:45,015
I've been going out with him.

407
00:28:45,975 --> 00:28:46,976
Happy now?

408
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:51,564
I'm sorry for keeping you in the dark.

409
00:28:52,898 --> 00:28:55,025
It was hard to keep it a secret.

410
00:28:55,109 --> 00:28:56,652
Now that we're open about it,

411
00:28:57,653 --> 00:28:59,113
it's a load off my chest.

412
00:29:00,156 --> 00:29:03,784
We'll be a good couple.
I look forward to your support.

413
00:29:11,208 --> 00:29:12,251
Sure.

414
00:29:16,589 --> 00:29:18,257
Jin-woo, give me a coffee.

415
00:29:18,340 --> 00:29:20,050
-Iced?
-Yes.

416
00:29:28,559 --> 00:29:30,644
Why didn't you tell me
you had a meeting here?

417
00:29:30,728 --> 00:29:32,146
I said I'd pick you up.

418
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:35,524
What...

419
00:29:37,359 --> 00:29:38,611
What are you doing now?

420
00:29:39,361 --> 00:29:41,447
I'm here to see you. Jin-woo as well.

421
00:29:45,284 --> 00:29:46,368
Hello.

422
00:29:46,452 --> 00:29:47,995
We did shake hands before.

423
00:29:48,078 --> 00:29:49,788
We haven't been properly introduced.

424
00:29:50,372 --> 00:29:51,373
I'm Noh Ju-wan.

425
00:29:54,668 --> 00:29:55,920
I'm Lee Su-hyeok.

426
00:29:56,003 --> 00:29:58,088
You didn't grab my hand tightly today.

427
00:30:00,424 --> 00:30:03,636
I heard from Bo-ra
that you became close through work.

428
00:30:04,094 --> 00:30:06,472
When I heard what you said that day,

429
00:30:07,890 --> 00:30:09,058
I thought you were dating.

430
00:30:09,141 --> 00:30:10,809
I was really on guard.

431
00:30:12,186 --> 00:30:13,812
It was just a wrong impression.

432
00:30:15,648 --> 00:30:17,900
It was just you being
passionate about your work.

433
00:30:20,694 --> 00:30:23,364
I reserved a restaurant for our dinner.

434
00:30:23,447 --> 00:30:25,574
You'll be surprised if you know where.

435
00:30:25,991 --> 00:30:28,035
It's the place where we used to go.

436
00:30:28,118 --> 00:30:31,163
You wanted to sit on the terrace
when it's nice outside.

437
00:30:31,247 --> 00:30:33,832
We were in the middle of a conversation.

438
00:30:36,252 --> 00:30:38,170
You need to talk more about work.

439
00:30:39,463 --> 00:30:41,799
I'll let you two talk first.

440
00:30:41,882 --> 00:30:43,592
I need to call someone anyway.

441
00:30:52,643 --> 00:30:53,686
You should go.

442
00:30:53,769 --> 00:30:55,521
I'm busy right now.

443
00:30:55,604 --> 00:30:57,147
-What?
-I said go.

444
00:30:58,649 --> 00:31:00,192
Okay. Got it.

445
00:31:00,276 --> 00:31:01,652
I'll talk with Jin-woo.

446
00:31:02,486 --> 00:31:03,654
Let's go when you're done.

447
00:31:14,748 --> 00:31:15,916
Why did you come?

448
00:31:16,458 --> 00:31:18,335
What do you mean? Shouldn't I come here?

449
00:31:18,419 --> 00:31:19,753
So,

450
00:31:19,837 --> 00:31:21,922
are you trying to get back with Bo-ra?

451
00:31:26,969 --> 00:31:27,970
Well...

452
00:31:38,897 --> 00:31:39,940
You look busy.

453
00:31:42,735 --> 00:31:47,031
By the way, do you always
do your work in this manner?

454
00:31:48,949 --> 00:31:50,492
What manner is that?

455
00:31:50,993 --> 00:31:55,623
I understand that it's common in Korea
to mix business with pleasure.

456
00:31:56,206 --> 00:31:59,293
But that usually leads to
unnecessary waste of emotions

457
00:31:59,376 --> 00:32:01,378
as well as avoidable mistakes.

458
00:32:02,963 --> 00:32:04,715
You're not getting to the point yet.

459
00:32:05,841 --> 00:32:07,801
You're really beating around the bush.

460
00:32:07,885 --> 00:32:09,595
I'm getting there.

461
00:32:09,678 --> 00:32:10,679
Do you...

462
00:32:12,056 --> 00:32:13,182
have feelings for Bo-ra?

463
00:32:18,812 --> 00:32:21,940
I don't think I need to
answer that question.

464
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:24,943
Right?

465
00:32:25,444 --> 00:32:27,696
Does an ex-boyfriend
have the right to do this?

466
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:33,202
I don't have the right for the moment.

467
00:32:33,911 --> 00:32:35,954
If you heard the broadcast,
you must be aware.

468
00:32:36,580 --> 00:32:38,123
I will get back together with Bo-ra.

469
00:32:38,957 --> 00:32:40,584
That is why I asked you.

470
00:32:41,293 --> 00:32:44,171
Fortunately, you didn't
give me any answer.

471
00:32:45,756 --> 00:32:47,466
If you said you had feelings for her,

472
00:32:47,549 --> 00:32:49,009
I was going to tell you not to.

473
00:32:49,093 --> 00:32:51,053
I was going to beg or persuade you.

474
00:32:54,014 --> 00:32:56,058
Don't look at me like I'm a loser.

475
00:32:56,517 --> 00:32:58,310
If I can start over with her,

476
00:32:58,686 --> 00:33:01,063
I'm willing to become a bigger loser.

477
00:33:01,814 --> 00:33:04,566
See? I was going to keep you in check
and make you give her up.

478
00:33:04,858 --> 00:33:06,360
But now I'm just begging you

479
00:33:07,361 --> 00:33:10,614
to stop swaying her.

480
00:33:12,032 --> 00:33:14,159
So you acknowledge that she's been swayed?

481
00:33:15,536 --> 00:33:17,037
You know already.

482
00:33:17,121 --> 00:33:18,914
When someone goes through a breakup

483
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:23,335
they can be swayed for a bit
by someone who comforted them.

484
00:33:24,461 --> 00:33:26,380
But taking advantage of that vulnerability

485
00:33:26,463 --> 00:33:28,257
is clearly not fair play.

486
00:33:31,218 --> 00:33:32,845
When we get back together

487
00:33:33,846 --> 00:33:35,848
and get married as we planned,

488
00:33:37,182 --> 00:33:38,267
Bo-ra...

489
00:33:39,143 --> 00:33:41,395
will have a hard time because of the fact

490
00:33:41,478 --> 00:33:44,523
that she was swayed for a moment.
I know that so well.

491
00:33:46,191 --> 00:33:47,818
That's why I'm telling you this.

492
00:34:33,697 --> 00:34:34,948
First of all, I'm so sorry.

493
00:34:35,783 --> 00:34:37,993
I know it could be very misleading.

494
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:39,661
Please let me explain.

495
00:34:39,745 --> 00:34:41,580
I didn't get back with him at all.

496
00:34:42,164 --> 00:34:44,041
He just wanted to be friends.

497
00:34:44,124 --> 00:34:45,125
And...

498
00:34:45,626 --> 00:34:47,377
I didn't plan to meet him here...

499
00:34:47,461 --> 00:34:49,338
No, there's no need.

500
00:34:51,006 --> 00:34:52,216
What?

501
00:34:53,675 --> 00:34:56,345
You don't need to explain
everything to me.

502
00:34:57,387 --> 00:34:59,890
I wasn't going to pry into
your love life, that's your privacy.

503
00:35:00,265 --> 00:35:02,810
I was just wondering
if there needs to be any changes

504
00:35:02,893 --> 00:35:05,479
to what we discussed
during the meeting last time.

505
00:35:05,562 --> 00:35:07,564
I was just asking for your confirmation.

506
00:35:12,402 --> 00:35:13,654
I see...

507
00:35:16,615 --> 00:35:18,033
Now it seems like

508
00:35:18,784 --> 00:35:20,786
we do need to make some changes.

509
00:35:22,496 --> 00:35:23,914
Let's wrap up the meeting today.

510
00:35:25,457 --> 00:35:26,458
I...

511
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:30,128
I'm afraid I'm interrupting your date.

512
00:35:30,420 --> 00:35:31,588
Let's talk in the meeting.

513
00:35:37,803 --> 00:35:39,763
This is for you on behalf of our company,

514
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:41,640
though it's a day late.

515
00:35:47,145 --> 00:35:49,273
I congratulate you on starting over.

516
00:35:50,065 --> 00:35:51,775
Your radio show and relationship.

517
00:36:03,161 --> 00:36:04,162
Are you done?

518
00:36:10,544 --> 00:36:11,545
Take care.

519
00:36:30,022 --> 00:36:32,733
We have a lot of time left
till our dinner reservation.

520
00:36:32,816 --> 00:36:35,235
What should we do?
Do we have enough time for a movie?

521
00:36:35,319 --> 00:36:37,905
-What are you doing? It's so childish.
-What?

522
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:40,699
You really don't know?

523
00:36:40,782 --> 00:36:42,659
I was having a meeting.

524
00:36:42,743 --> 00:36:44,453
How could you interrupt that?

525
00:36:44,870 --> 00:36:48,123
Well, I just...
Since I'm acquainted with him,

526
00:36:48,206 --> 00:36:51,293
I didn't want to act like a stranger,
so I said hi.

527
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:54,796
-It made you uncomfortable.
-I know you did that on purpose

528
00:36:55,339 --> 00:36:57,674
to mislead him about our relationship.

529
00:36:58,258 --> 00:36:59,551
What's there to mislead?

530
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:03,013
You said he's just a close colleague.

531
00:37:03,889 --> 00:37:05,057
Isn't he?

532
00:37:06,433 --> 00:37:09,645
Or... do you have feelings for him?

533
00:37:11,688 --> 00:37:12,940
What?

534
00:37:18,528 --> 00:37:20,447
If you can't answer, never mind.

535
00:37:20,530 --> 00:37:22,491
He couldn't answer
the same question either.

536
00:37:22,574 --> 00:37:24,159
If you can't too,

537
00:37:24,868 --> 00:37:27,371
there's nothing to worry about, right?

538
00:37:34,252 --> 00:37:35,253
Fine.

539
00:37:35,671 --> 00:37:38,840
Let me reject you in person.
I can't have dinner with you.

540
00:37:38,924 --> 00:37:40,050
Bye.

541
00:37:51,812 --> 00:37:54,272
I swallowed my pride,
and I'm making an effort.

542
00:37:54,356 --> 00:37:56,274
But why now?

543
00:37:56,775 --> 00:37:59,069
You said you hated me.
You were sick and tired of me.

544
00:37:59,152 --> 00:38:02,239
Now that it's over, you feel sad?
Are you jealous I'd see someone else?

545
00:38:02,322 --> 00:38:03,907
Fine. I hated it.

546
00:38:03,991 --> 00:38:05,534
Now that it's over, I can't move on.

547
00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:08,078
The thought of you with someone else
is driving me crazy!

548
00:38:13,333 --> 00:38:14,459
Bo-ra.

549
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:16,294
Listen to me.

550
00:38:17,045 --> 00:38:18,171
I love you.

551
00:38:18,463 --> 00:38:20,674
But what I can't possibly stand right now

552
00:38:20,757 --> 00:38:24,177
is the fact that you're swayed
by a guy who doesn't even like you.

553
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:30,767
We should have just
gotten married back then.

554
00:38:33,061 --> 00:38:35,022
What on earth are you talking about?

555
00:38:36,481 --> 00:38:39,776
Like you said, I don't know you well,

556
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:41,319
but I do know one thing.

557
00:38:41,862 --> 00:38:44,031
You're not emotional enough
to be swayed by a guy

558
00:38:44,114 --> 00:38:45,699
who gives you such little assurance.

559
00:38:46,867 --> 00:38:48,160
Am I wrong?

560
00:38:52,289 --> 00:38:53,665
It's true, Bo-ra.

561
00:38:55,250 --> 00:38:58,128
If you do this, we can't even be friends.

562
00:39:00,297 --> 00:39:01,965
I didn't want that in the first place.

563
00:39:02,591 --> 00:39:03,842
How can we be friends?

564
00:39:04,342 --> 00:39:05,510
Should I say it again?

565
00:39:06,053 --> 00:39:07,971
I love you.

566
00:39:08,055 --> 00:39:09,931
How can we possibly become friends?

567
00:39:18,648 --> 00:39:19,691
Hey.

568
00:39:19,775 --> 00:39:21,234
How did it go with Deborah?

569
00:39:21,318 --> 00:39:22,819
Do they seem to be back together?

570
00:39:24,946 --> 00:39:26,031
Yeah.

571
00:39:27,032 --> 00:39:28,450
That's amazing.

572
00:39:28,533 --> 00:39:31,495
All right. This is more like it!

573
00:39:31,578 --> 00:39:32,913
Do you hear that sound?

574
00:39:34,081 --> 00:39:36,541
The sound of printing
1st, 2nd, 3rd editions, right?

575
00:39:37,584 --> 00:39:38,960
What's with all this?

576
00:39:39,044 --> 00:39:41,797
Aren't we supposed to go for
an open ending, not a reunion?

577
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:43,840
Things are different now.

578
00:39:43,924 --> 00:39:46,009
I didn't like an open ending
from the beginning.

579
00:39:46,093 --> 00:39:47,302
Nothing beats a happy ending.

580
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:48,762
You call this a happy ending?

581
00:39:48,845 --> 00:39:50,180
An ending like that?

582
00:39:50,972 --> 00:39:53,475
Is it all a happy ending
if the book sells well?

583
00:39:54,184 --> 00:39:55,644
That's not what I meant.

584
00:39:55,727 --> 00:39:57,562
It's what the writer wanted.

585
00:39:57,896 --> 00:39:59,815
What did she want the most from day one?

586
00:39:59,898 --> 00:40:02,984
She wanted to get her ex back.

587
00:40:04,069 --> 00:40:07,489
Also, how many couples do not
go through a breakup before marriage?

588
00:40:07,823 --> 00:40:09,699
They must have learned something from it.

589
00:40:09,783 --> 00:40:12,160
And they get back together stronger
after staying apart.

590
00:40:12,244 --> 00:40:14,496
Indeed, it is a happy ending.

591
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:21,545
So we have to change
the publishing plan for Deborah's book?

592
00:40:21,628 --> 00:40:23,004
You heard him.

593
00:40:23,088 --> 00:40:26,174
I made all the marketing plans
with the current concept.

594
00:40:26,925 --> 00:40:29,261
Then what was that meeting for
in the first place?

595
00:40:29,344 --> 00:40:31,638
There's nothing we can do.
It is what it is.

596
00:40:31,721 --> 00:40:34,099
He insisted that he's not a geezer.

597
00:40:34,182 --> 00:40:35,600
But why is he acting like one?

598
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:38,562
By the way, U-ri.

599
00:40:39,062 --> 00:40:40,230
What do you think?

600
00:40:40,313 --> 00:40:42,691
Pardon? About what?

601
00:40:43,233 --> 00:40:44,484
Why do you even ask?

602
00:40:44,568 --> 00:40:46,695
She should be on her boyfriend's side.

603
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:50,740
What? Boyfriend?

604
00:40:51,158 --> 00:40:53,577
U-ri. We all know about you two.

605
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:55,078
You're dating him, right?

606
00:40:55,162 --> 00:40:57,414
You could just tell us.
What's the big deal?

607
00:40:58,665 --> 00:41:00,500
Me and Sang-jin?

608
00:41:00,584 --> 00:41:01,585
Yes.

609
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:02,711
No.

610
00:41:03,503 --> 00:41:06,798
Come on. I wasn't going to
bring it up, but to be honest,

611
00:41:06,882 --> 00:41:09,593
you got hired by pulling strings.
Everyone here knows that.

612
00:41:10,552 --> 00:41:12,637
That's true.

613
00:41:14,514 --> 00:41:16,683
No, what I mean is...

614
00:41:16,766 --> 00:41:18,518
By the way, are you okay with it?

615
00:41:18,935 --> 00:41:20,562
You know Sang-jin got divorced.

616
00:41:20,645 --> 00:41:21,938
It should be okay.

617
00:41:22,022 --> 00:41:23,607
He's from a very wealthy family.

618
00:41:23,690 --> 00:41:26,067
A building owner.
A born-with-a-silver-spoon president.

619
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:29,321
U-ri, you must've watched too many dramas.

620
00:41:29,404 --> 00:41:32,157
Or is it more like Cinderella?

621
00:41:35,076 --> 00:41:38,872
It's nothing like that.
It's a misunderstanding.

622
00:41:38,955 --> 00:41:40,832
I won't force you to answer,

623
00:41:40,916 --> 00:41:43,668
but U-ri, please make one thing clear.

624
00:41:43,752 --> 00:41:47,255
You won't become full-time
before Hyun-seok, right?

625
00:41:48,465 --> 00:41:51,259
How would I know that?

626
00:41:51,343 --> 00:41:53,094
No way. Is it all arranged already?

627
00:41:53,845 --> 00:41:55,555
Then, is it all right to do this?

628
00:41:55,639 --> 00:41:57,265
Shouldn't we get on her good side?

629
00:41:57,349 --> 00:42:00,602
It's really nothing like that.

630
00:42:00,685 --> 00:42:01,770
It's not.

631
00:42:01,853 --> 00:42:03,438
In that case,

632
00:42:03,980 --> 00:42:06,775
is Sang-jin hitting on you

633
00:42:06,858 --> 00:42:08,693
using the job
or your full-time employment?

634
00:42:08,777 --> 00:42:10,237
No.

635
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,739
-Sounds true.
-You can tell us if that's the case.

636
00:42:13,198 --> 00:42:15,659
Do tell us. It's really okay.

637
00:42:15,742 --> 00:42:16,993
No.

638
00:42:17,077 --> 00:42:18,954
That's what the employees said?

639
00:42:19,579 --> 00:42:20,997
And U-ri couldn't say a thing?

640
00:42:29,923 --> 00:42:31,132
Sang-jin.

641
00:42:31,758 --> 00:42:33,343
You know you always say that

642
00:42:33,426 --> 00:42:36,513
you do what can be criticized for,
but never do what you'd be ashamed of.

643
00:42:37,472 --> 00:42:38,848
It's not that, right?

644
00:42:40,183 --> 00:42:42,727
You didn't do something
you'd be ashamed of, right?

645
00:42:45,438 --> 00:42:46,439
Right.

646
00:42:48,149 --> 00:42:50,443
If they hear
the president kept hitting on her,

647
00:42:50,527 --> 00:42:53,488
they wouldn't blame the female employee
for flirting with him anymore.

648
00:42:53,822 --> 00:42:55,991
Okay, let's go with that.

649
00:42:56,074 --> 00:42:58,660
Where is that coming from?
How is that a solution?

650
00:42:59,286 --> 00:43:00,578
What should I do then?

651
00:43:01,705 --> 00:43:04,624
She just started her career.
Should I let her take all the heat?

652
00:43:54,049 --> 00:43:55,675
Let's call it a day.

653
00:43:55,759 --> 00:43:57,927
-Let's go.
-Okay.

654
00:44:02,057 --> 00:44:03,141
You see...

655
00:44:04,642 --> 00:44:06,644
There's something I need to tell you.

656
00:44:08,772 --> 00:44:11,649
It was just me.

657
00:44:12,484 --> 00:44:14,527
I had a crush on Mr. Sang-jin.

658
00:44:16,738 --> 00:44:20,742
I got dumped even before saying
how I feel about him.

659
00:44:22,369 --> 00:44:26,873
I don't think that is wrong.

660
00:44:27,749 --> 00:44:31,753
Because you don't need to be qualified
to like someone.

661
00:44:34,381 --> 00:44:39,427
But now I come to think
that I'm probably not qualified.

662
00:44:41,554 --> 00:44:45,517
Also, I didn't know Sang-jin was rich.

663
00:44:46,184 --> 00:44:47,644
I really had no idea.

664
00:44:48,645 --> 00:44:52,565
Though I think that'd make no difference
to the way I feel about him.

665
00:44:52,649 --> 00:44:54,567
That is not why I had feelings for him.

666
00:44:55,610 --> 00:44:56,903
Other than that,

667
00:44:58,113 --> 00:45:00,573
there were so many things
I liked about him.

668
00:45:03,701 --> 00:45:04,911
As for myself,

669
00:45:07,372 --> 00:45:09,707
I prefer books to dramas.

670
00:45:10,458 --> 00:45:12,919
That's why I got a job at this company.

671
00:45:13,545 --> 00:45:15,797
My favorite books are

672
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:19,342
Anne of Green Gables, Daddy-Long-Legs,

673
00:45:20,677 --> 00:45:22,387
not Cinderella.

674
00:45:45,827 --> 00:45:47,078
Let me keep this short.

675
00:45:49,873 --> 00:45:52,250
I need to straighten something out
as vice president.

676
00:45:54,586 --> 00:45:56,296
At Jinlee Publishing,

677
00:45:56,379 --> 00:45:59,757
as you know, we've hired office assistance

678
00:45:59,841 --> 00:46:02,010
and management support positions
year-round.

679
00:46:02,093 --> 00:46:05,430
That said, in the process of hiring U-ri,

680
00:46:05,513 --> 00:46:07,974
there were no
procedural issues whatsoever.

681
00:46:08,975 --> 00:46:10,518
As for switching to full-time,

682
00:46:10,602 --> 00:46:13,646
the decision will be made
solely upon performance reviews.

683
00:46:13,730 --> 00:46:17,025
In addition, office gossip
and unsubstantiated hearsay

684
00:46:17,108 --> 00:46:18,568
about your co-worker

685
00:46:19,319 --> 00:46:21,404
is clearly workplace bullying.

686
00:46:22,572 --> 00:46:23,698
Last but not least,

687
00:46:24,616 --> 00:46:26,242
as for confessions and apologies,

688
00:46:28,077 --> 00:46:31,581
when you think it's late, it's too late.

689
00:46:32,916 --> 00:46:34,250
That's all.

690
00:46:34,334 --> 00:46:36,169
Enjoy the rest of your day, everyone.

691
00:46:36,252 --> 00:46:37,378
See you tomorrow.

692
00:46:38,379 --> 00:46:39,547
-See you tomorrow.
-Bye.

693
00:46:39,631 --> 00:46:41,007
Let's go, Sang-jin.

694
00:46:43,551 --> 00:46:45,261
He does all the cool stuff.

695
00:46:50,058 --> 00:46:51,184
Bye.

696
00:47:00,985 --> 00:47:02,070
U-ri.

697
00:47:02,529 --> 00:47:05,865
Sorry. I'm so sorry
that I can't find the right words.

698
00:47:06,491 --> 00:47:08,826
I thought you were dating.

699
00:47:08,910 --> 00:47:11,120
We were upset
since we thought you lied to us.

700
00:47:11,204 --> 00:47:12,830
It's just how we felt.

701
00:47:12,914 --> 00:47:15,959
Anyway, there's no excuse for it.
We were so wrong.

702
00:47:16,042 --> 00:47:18,461
It's about time for me
to get a chance to be full-time.

703
00:47:18,545 --> 00:47:20,547
I was over-sensitive. I'm so sorry.

704
00:47:20,630 --> 00:47:22,549
You don't need to accept my apology now.

705
00:47:22,924 --> 00:47:24,884
No, apology accepted.

706
00:47:24,968 --> 00:47:26,302
I'm sorry, and thank you.

707
00:47:26,386 --> 00:47:28,763
Shall we have a beer together?

708
00:47:28,846 --> 00:47:31,307
-It's on me.
-No, we got a company card.

709
00:47:31,391 --> 00:47:33,977
-Let's go together, U-ri.
-I'll pack my stuff then.

710
00:47:38,856 --> 00:47:40,441
You have a stomachache?

711
00:47:40,525 --> 00:47:41,901
Isn't it indigestion?

712
00:47:41,985 --> 00:47:44,946
I don't know.
It kind of feels like indigestion.

713
00:47:45,989 --> 00:47:47,740
Maybe I ate too much today.

714
00:47:49,742 --> 00:47:50,785
Right.

715
00:47:50,868 --> 00:47:54,998
You had French toast,
waffles, strawberries and a lot of cakes.

716
00:47:56,916 --> 00:48:00,253
You could win an eating competition.

717
00:48:01,504 --> 00:48:03,673
SANITARY PADS

718
00:48:07,677 --> 00:48:09,012
What should we buy?

719
00:48:09,095 --> 00:48:11,180
Cola? Sparkling water?

720
00:48:11,723 --> 00:48:13,891
Or digestive medicine?

721
00:48:16,644 --> 00:48:18,855
Where's a pregnancy test?

722
00:48:39,167 --> 00:48:41,294
We have three minutes to think.

723
00:48:41,377 --> 00:48:43,546
Let's think what we should do
if it's two lines.

724
00:48:44,672 --> 00:48:46,174
What do you mean? Of course we...

725
00:48:46,257 --> 00:48:47,508
Not of course.

726
00:48:48,092 --> 00:48:49,385
Whether to give birth or not,

727
00:48:49,469 --> 00:48:52,388
whether to raise a baby by myself
or together, we should make a choice.

728
00:48:56,684 --> 00:48:58,436
I made my decision.

729
00:48:58,519 --> 00:48:59,646
Let's get married.

730
00:49:02,565 --> 00:49:04,651
Don't be impulsive. Think.

731
00:49:05,026 --> 00:49:06,444
I will think about it, too.

732
00:49:06,527 --> 00:49:07,987
You do the thinking. I'm done.

733
00:49:08,863 --> 00:49:10,114
I want to marry you anyway.

734
00:49:10,198 --> 00:49:12,492
If it's sooner,
it's all the better for me.

735
00:49:12,575 --> 00:49:14,744
Because we'd be able to
be together longer.

736
00:50:39,036 --> 00:50:41,414
I can't believe I'm becoming a daddy.

737
00:50:42,832 --> 00:50:46,627
I feel like I'm on top of the world.
I mean it.

738
00:50:46,711 --> 00:50:47,879
Awesome!

739
00:50:51,841 --> 00:50:53,092
What's wrong?

740
00:50:53,426 --> 00:50:54,469
You hesitated.

741
00:50:54,552 --> 00:50:56,220
You hesitated. You just did.

742
00:50:56,846 --> 00:50:58,556
No, I'm really thrilled.

743
00:50:58,639 --> 00:50:59,974
I feel like I could fly now.

744
00:51:00,057 --> 00:51:03,227
When you are extremely happy,
you could go numb all of a sudden.

745
00:51:03,311 --> 00:51:04,437
I mean it!

746
00:51:07,064 --> 00:51:08,357
Believe me.

747
00:51:13,905 --> 00:51:16,908
So did you make a decision?

748
00:51:17,700 --> 00:51:18,951
I don't know.

749
00:51:19,410 --> 00:51:21,579
I shouldn't have a belly bump
in my wedding dress.

750
00:51:26,167 --> 00:51:27,460
I'm so happy!

751
00:51:31,297 --> 00:51:32,548
Are you hungry again?

752
00:51:33,257 --> 00:51:34,342
Yes.

753
00:51:34,801 --> 00:51:36,469
But I'm not the one who's hungry.

754
00:51:38,221 --> 00:51:40,014
I shouldn't let our baby feel hungry.

755
00:51:40,097 --> 00:51:41,140
Wait up.

756
00:52:39,156 --> 00:52:40,157
Honey, guess what...

757
00:52:40,241 --> 00:52:41,325
No.

758
00:52:42,743 --> 00:52:44,579
Why are you saying no?
You don't know what.

759
00:52:44,662 --> 00:52:46,205
Whatever it is, it's a no.

760
00:52:47,748 --> 00:52:50,126
Well, the thing is,

761
00:52:50,209 --> 00:52:52,336
you know Sang-cheol, he...

762
00:52:52,420 --> 00:52:54,171
I said no!

763
00:52:54,255 --> 00:52:56,966
You didn't even hear me out.
Can't let me finish my sentence?

764
00:52:57,049 --> 00:52:58,676
I'm saying no to a caravan.

765
00:52:59,552 --> 00:53:01,762
What, Sang-cheol told you
to buy it from him?

766
00:53:01,846 --> 00:53:03,347
-That it's a steal?
-Yes.

767
00:53:03,431 --> 00:53:04,640
Do you know why?

768
00:53:04,724 --> 00:53:07,268
Because his wife
told him she'll divorce him

769
00:53:07,351 --> 00:53:08,644
if he doesn't sell it,

770
00:53:08,728 --> 00:53:11,230
because she's had enough.

771
00:53:11,314 --> 00:53:14,483
If you bring it here,
do you think I'd say nothing?

772
00:53:17,278 --> 00:53:19,280
You're unbelievable.

773
00:53:19,363 --> 00:53:22,408
Games, cameras, figurines, golf,

774
00:53:22,491 --> 00:53:25,202
fishing, and now it's camping?

775
00:53:30,583 --> 00:53:31,959
-Well, still...
-No.

776
00:53:32,043 --> 00:53:33,294
-No.
-I said no.

777
00:53:33,377 --> 00:53:34,587
It's a no-no.

778
00:53:34,962 --> 00:53:37,173
Okay, I won't. Enough.

779
00:53:38,382 --> 00:53:39,383
No to everything...

780
00:53:39,842 --> 00:53:40,927
You heard me.

781
00:53:45,932 --> 00:53:47,892
Where's my phone?

782
00:53:48,726 --> 00:53:50,519
Out of the way. Aren't you sitting on it?

783
00:53:50,603 --> 00:53:52,521
I don't know. Look carefully.

784
00:53:52,605 --> 00:53:53,856
Is it downstairs?

785
00:53:57,818 --> 00:53:59,904
-Call me!
-Okay.

786
00:54:06,661 --> 00:54:07,912
Found it!

787
00:54:31,519 --> 00:54:32,979
Yu-jeong.

788
00:54:36,774 --> 00:54:40,695
So you've been
letting Jin-ho stay downstairs all along?

789
00:54:41,112 --> 00:54:43,072
You could have told me so, why...

790
00:54:46,283 --> 00:54:47,493
Why?

791
00:54:48,411 --> 00:54:50,162
Why couldn't you tell me?

792
00:54:52,540 --> 00:54:54,959
He needed to crash for a short time
till he got a place.

793
00:54:55,042 --> 00:54:56,711
So I just didn't tell you.

794
00:54:57,128 --> 00:54:58,295
-Right?
-Yes.

795
00:54:58,379 --> 00:55:02,008
But finding a place is taking
longer than I thought.

796
00:55:03,634 --> 00:55:04,802
Lead the way.

797
00:55:05,678 --> 00:55:07,888
-To where?
-You know where.

798
00:55:09,515 --> 00:55:11,642
-But...
-Lead the way.

799
00:55:12,518 --> 00:55:13,602
-Privacy...
-Hurry up.

800
00:55:41,172 --> 00:55:42,465
What is this?

801
00:55:44,675 --> 00:55:47,136
Oh, my gosh...

802
00:55:47,845 --> 00:55:48,846
What is all this?

803
00:55:49,972 --> 00:55:51,182
I don't know.

804
00:55:51,265 --> 00:55:53,559
What is all this? I have no clue.

805
00:55:54,143 --> 00:55:56,062
Jin-ho. It's all yours, right?

806
00:55:57,813 --> 00:55:58,981
Yes.

807
00:56:01,776 --> 00:56:03,194
Seriously, cut it out.

808
00:56:04,403 --> 00:56:06,030
When are you going to stop lying?

809
00:56:06,447 --> 00:56:08,199
What else did you lie about?

810
00:56:08,282 --> 00:56:10,326
You could just say you two are dating.

811
00:56:10,409 --> 00:56:12,328
Is there more that I don't know about?

812
00:56:12,411 --> 00:56:14,705
Did you hide a girl in here?

813
00:56:17,625 --> 00:56:19,835
Bo-mi.

814
00:56:21,504 --> 00:56:22,838
-What is it?
-Are you okay?

815
00:56:23,714 --> 00:56:25,132
You must be scared.

816
00:56:25,216 --> 00:56:26,383
Is our baby okay?

817
00:56:31,263 --> 00:56:32,306
It's okay.

818
00:56:38,938 --> 00:56:40,314
Are you pregnant?

819
00:56:51,075 --> 00:56:52,409
I can't believe this.

820
00:57:00,501 --> 00:57:01,544
BO-RA

821
00:57:02,253 --> 00:57:03,963
No.

822
00:57:04,046 --> 00:57:05,923
Don't pick it up. Please. I'm begging you.

823
00:57:06,006 --> 00:57:07,341
Let go.

824
00:57:07,424 --> 00:57:09,552
No. She's really going to kill me.

825
00:57:09,635 --> 00:57:10,886
This isn't right. Let go.

826
00:57:11,303 --> 00:57:12,304
Let go.

827
00:57:13,889 --> 00:57:15,724
Don't tell her, or I will throw this.

828
00:57:15,808 --> 00:57:17,560
I can really throw it. I will.

829
00:57:17,643 --> 00:57:19,061
No!

830
00:57:19,145 --> 00:57:21,021
Honey, put down your phone.

831
00:57:22,189 --> 00:57:23,691
It's really expensive.

832
00:57:23,774 --> 00:57:25,693
Please, Yu-jeong.

833
00:57:25,776 --> 00:57:27,319
-I'm going to throw it.
-No!

834
00:57:29,446 --> 00:57:31,282
All right.

835
00:57:31,740 --> 00:57:34,160
I'll talk to her briefly and hang up.

836
00:57:34,243 --> 00:57:35,744
So that she won't call again.

837
00:57:35,828 --> 00:57:36,871
Sounds good?

838
00:57:36,954 --> 00:57:39,498
Then give me the phone
and talk on the speakerphone.

839
00:57:42,877 --> 00:57:43,878
Give it.

840
00:57:54,513 --> 00:57:55,764
Hey.

841
00:57:56,140 --> 00:58:00,686
Hey, I shouldn't be asking a married woman
to come out this late at night, right?

842
00:58:01,812 --> 00:58:03,439
Why? You need a drink?

843
00:58:08,777 --> 00:58:10,571
Bo-ra. Hurry here! Bo-mi's pregnant!

844
00:58:17,786 --> 00:58:19,038
What did she say?

845
00:58:20,748 --> 00:58:22,166
"Bo-ra, hurry here."

846
00:58:22,917 --> 00:58:25,502
"Bo-mi's fragrant?"

847
00:58:26,879 --> 00:58:28,005
What did she say?

848
00:58:38,766 --> 00:58:39,808
So...

849
00:58:42,937 --> 00:58:43,979
you're saying...

850
00:58:47,024 --> 00:58:48,525
she's pregnant?

851
00:58:57,368 --> 00:58:58,786
Come on out.

852
00:58:58,869 --> 00:59:00,913
No, I won't go.

853
00:59:02,373 --> 00:59:04,333
If not, what are you going to do here?

854
00:59:04,416 --> 00:59:05,542
Come with me.

855
00:59:06,460 --> 00:59:07,544
Bo-ra...

856
00:59:13,384 --> 00:59:15,594
-Come.
-What's the matter with you?

857
00:59:15,678 --> 00:59:18,055
Why are you acting like
I did something wrong?

858
00:59:18,138 --> 00:59:19,473
You...

859
00:59:20,474 --> 00:59:22,810
Hey, go and talk to her at home.

860
00:59:23,477 --> 00:59:24,728
You should go with her.

861
00:59:40,411 --> 00:59:41,787
Hey.

862
00:59:42,830 --> 00:59:43,998
Stay here.

863
00:59:56,552 --> 00:59:57,553
Hey...

864
01:00:10,357 --> 01:00:11,984
How shocking.

865
01:00:14,111 --> 01:00:15,362
What was all that?

866
01:00:15,446 --> 01:00:17,865
Why are you following me up?
Go play downstairs like you do.

867
01:00:18,365 --> 01:00:20,075
Come on.

868
01:00:20,617 --> 01:00:21,618
You want me to go?

869
01:00:23,370 --> 01:00:25,956
I just played video games
and watched soccer sometimes.

870
01:00:27,791 --> 01:00:28,876
I'm sorry.

871
01:00:30,502 --> 01:00:31,837
Did I complain?

872
01:00:31,920 --> 01:00:33,839
Why do you lie to me?

873
01:00:33,922 --> 01:00:35,632
You keep lying to me.

874
01:00:35,716 --> 01:00:37,718
What lie?

875
01:00:42,181 --> 01:00:43,307
All right.

876
01:00:43,932 --> 01:00:47,061
I'll stop everything. That'll do, right?

877
01:00:47,436 --> 01:00:48,771
"That'll do"?

878
01:00:51,732 --> 01:00:55,694
How am I supposed to believe you now?
If you needed alone time so badly

879
01:00:55,778 --> 01:00:58,030
that you had to lie,
why did you even marry me?

880
01:00:59,156 --> 01:01:02,242
Right, because I asked you to.

881
01:01:02,576 --> 01:01:03,911
You didn't even propose to me.

882
01:01:03,994 --> 01:01:05,829
You married me
just because I asked you, right?

883
01:01:05,913 --> 01:01:07,289
That's why you're doing this.

884
01:01:08,290 --> 01:01:10,918
Until when are you going to
talk about the proposal?

885
01:01:13,962 --> 01:01:14,963
Do you love me?

886
01:01:16,173 --> 01:01:17,424
Do you even love me?

887
01:01:18,175 --> 01:01:19,593
You said you won't believe me.

888
01:01:19,676 --> 01:01:21,011
That's right.

889
01:01:21,678 --> 01:01:24,306
I can't believe you anymore. I won't.

890
01:01:24,390 --> 01:01:26,266
Because you've lost my trust.

891
01:01:26,350 --> 01:01:29,103
Where's the man that I wanted to marry?

892
01:01:29,728 --> 01:01:33,273
The man who put his phone in a waterproof
pack not to miss my call while showering.

893
01:01:33,357 --> 01:01:36,485
The man who let the last bus leave
and stayed all night together

894
01:01:36,568 --> 01:01:37,945
and was still sad to say bye.

895
01:01:38,028 --> 01:01:39,655
The man who used to do a video call

896
01:01:39,738 --> 01:01:42,074
24 hours 'cause you missed me
when I was studying abroad.

897
01:01:42,157 --> 01:01:44,535
That's the man I married.

898
01:01:47,704 --> 01:01:49,456
But now, you're just...

899
01:01:50,457 --> 01:01:53,585
You're just a selfish,
emotionally detached guy.

900
01:01:54,086 --> 01:01:55,712
Hey. Yang Jin-woo.

901
01:01:56,922 --> 01:01:58,549
You've really changed.

902
01:01:59,716 --> 01:02:00,801
Are you aware of that?

903
01:02:01,552 --> 01:02:03,387
Yes, so have you.

904
01:02:04,221 --> 01:02:06,348
-What?
-You think you haven't changed?

905
01:02:07,015 --> 01:02:08,684
You always complain about whatever I say.

906
01:02:08,767 --> 01:02:10,853
You hate whatever I do.
You say no to everything.

907
01:02:10,936 --> 01:02:14,022
That is why I can't say anything.
Why would I? You won't listen anyway.

908
01:02:14,690 --> 01:02:16,400
Did I? When? About what?

909
01:02:16,483 --> 01:02:18,193
Am I wrong? "Stop playing games."

910
01:02:18,277 --> 01:02:19,403
"Biking is dangerous."

911
01:02:19,486 --> 01:02:20,946
Fishing? You hate everything!

912
01:02:21,029 --> 01:02:23,532
"Golf? A guy like you?"
"Don't you dare invest in stocks."

913
01:02:23,615 --> 01:02:25,492
"I'll divorce you
if you buy cryptocurrency."

914
01:02:25,576 --> 01:02:26,952
Then what can I ever do?

915
01:02:27,035 --> 01:02:28,245
All I should do is work?

916
01:02:28,328 --> 01:02:30,372
Work, home, work, home,
no time for myself?

917
01:02:30,456 --> 01:02:31,957
I need alone time.

918
01:02:32,040 --> 01:02:33,584
Just a little bit of alone time,

919
01:02:33,667 --> 01:02:34,918
I just need a little bit.

920
01:02:35,002 --> 01:02:36,545
What did I do so wrong?

921
01:02:42,509 --> 01:02:43,677
Then what about us?

922
01:02:44,136 --> 01:02:46,722
What? What about us?

923
01:02:47,848 --> 01:02:49,725
Do we ever spend time together?

924
01:02:52,895 --> 01:02:54,021
Jin-woo.

925
01:02:54,730 --> 01:02:57,483
In the morning, we are in a rush
and busy all day at work.

926
01:02:57,816 --> 01:03:00,527
In the evening, after dinner and
cleaning up, we just pass out.

927
01:03:01,570 --> 01:03:04,990
But you complain
you don't have alone time for yourself.

928
01:03:05,073 --> 01:03:07,451
You're not bothered about
not having time with me?

929
01:03:11,079 --> 01:03:12,789
I guess you aren't. I am.

930
01:03:13,540 --> 01:03:15,042
If you put it that way...

931
01:03:16,210 --> 01:03:17,753
Well, we will be together

932
01:03:18,587 --> 01:03:20,255
for the rest of our lives, so...

933
01:03:20,339 --> 01:03:21,757
Is that so?

934
01:03:22,966 --> 01:03:24,676
That's what you think.

935
01:03:27,846 --> 01:03:30,849
So you lie to me
'cause I'd give you an earful,

936
01:03:31,308 --> 01:03:33,644
you don't do it with me
'cause you could some other time.

937
01:03:33,727 --> 01:03:36,688
We'll be together for life,
so you can put off spending time with me.

938
01:03:36,772 --> 01:03:38,357
I'm your lowest priority.

939
01:03:40,150 --> 01:03:41,610
I see that's what you think.

940
01:03:44,530 --> 01:03:45,781
By the way,

941
01:03:47,741 --> 01:03:50,244
who said we'll be together for life?

942
01:03:53,580 --> 01:03:55,874
What's that supposed to mean?

943
01:03:56,875 --> 01:03:58,001
I just wonder

944
01:03:58,961 --> 01:04:01,964
if living together for life like this
is really meaningful.

945
01:04:02,047 --> 01:04:03,674
That crossed my mind.

946
01:04:03,757 --> 01:04:06,176
How can you...

947
01:04:07,886 --> 01:04:09,721
I'll sleep somewhere else. Okay?

948
01:04:33,787 --> 01:04:35,330
Let me crash here tonight.

949
01:04:45,173 --> 01:04:47,676
I'm sorry, Jin-woo. It's all my fault.

950
01:04:50,012 --> 01:04:53,390
You should have told me.
You lied and made things get out of hand.

951
01:04:53,890 --> 01:04:54,975
Turn off the light.

952
01:05:04,318 --> 01:05:05,944
-Good night.
-You, too.

953
01:05:42,856 --> 01:05:44,191
Hello, Ms. Yeon.

954
01:05:44,274 --> 01:05:46,693
-Hi, U-ri.
-Let me take you to the conference room.

955
01:05:59,456 --> 01:06:02,668
Mr. Han. Ms. Yeon is here.

956
01:06:02,751 --> 01:06:03,835
Okay.

957
01:06:04,419 --> 01:06:05,545
U-ri.

958
01:06:07,297 --> 01:06:08,298
Yes?

959
01:06:11,635 --> 01:06:14,054
Well... Are you all right?

960
01:06:14,846 --> 01:06:17,224
Pardon? Why?

961
01:06:18,433 --> 01:06:19,476
No, I was just...

962
01:06:20,560 --> 01:06:23,855
I was worried about you.

963
01:06:24,398 --> 01:06:26,108
Did you talk it out with your co-workers?

964
01:06:26,191 --> 01:06:28,735
I hope you don't feel
uncomfortable around me.

965
01:06:31,238 --> 01:06:34,574
They apologized to me
and we cleared up the misunderstandings.

966
01:06:34,658 --> 01:06:37,077
And I'm all right.

967
01:06:37,160 --> 01:06:40,580
I owe you an apology.

968
01:06:40,997 --> 01:06:44,835
I shouldn't have made you uncomfortable
by expressing my feelings.

969
01:06:45,502 --> 01:06:47,629
But you don't have to worry about it.

970
01:06:47,713 --> 01:06:50,132
It will never happen again.

971
01:06:50,215 --> 01:06:52,426
I got over you now.

972
01:06:53,218 --> 01:06:55,262
And I'm cool.

973
01:06:58,306 --> 01:06:59,391
Well, then.

974
01:07:15,615 --> 01:07:17,451
Let's start the meeting in ten minutes.

975
01:07:17,534 --> 01:07:19,911
I have something
to discuss with her first.

976
01:07:19,995 --> 01:07:21,413
-Okay.
-Okay.

977
01:07:50,776 --> 01:07:53,069
When can I expect to receive a draft?

978
01:07:54,738 --> 01:07:57,157
By now, I need a specific timeline.

979
01:07:57,949 --> 01:07:59,701
But you won't share your draft,

980
01:08:00,243 --> 01:08:01,787
it's hard to get things moving.

981
01:08:05,624 --> 01:08:07,167
I only have the ending part left.

982
01:08:08,251 --> 01:08:09,961
I need some time to mull over it.

983
01:08:11,379 --> 01:08:14,299
So you aren't sure about the deadline.
Is that what you mean?

984
01:08:14,716 --> 01:08:15,717
Yes.

985
01:08:18,804 --> 01:08:21,640
When a writer can't decide an ending,
in most of the cases,

986
01:08:22,098 --> 01:08:24,768
it's because the ending doesn't
seem convincing to readers.

987
01:08:27,979 --> 01:08:29,773
If it's not convincing to yourself,

988
01:08:29,856 --> 01:08:31,733
how are you supposed to
convince the readers?

989
01:08:35,862 --> 01:08:37,614
You got out of a beat-up car,

990
01:08:37,697 --> 01:08:40,367
but you bother to repair and
get back in it, such a happy ending...

991
01:08:42,911 --> 01:08:44,996
It is not a very convincing ending.

992
01:08:51,545 --> 01:08:53,880
It is easy to criticize destructively.

993
01:08:53,964 --> 01:08:56,842
How should I change the ending?

994
01:08:57,509 --> 01:09:00,136
I got out of the beat-up car,
and get hit by an even more beat-up car?

995
01:09:00,679 --> 01:09:02,889
Or I sold a beat-up car
and got a Mercedes.

996
01:09:02,973 --> 01:09:04,307
Turns out it was salvaged?

997
01:09:04,391 --> 01:09:06,560
I got totally screwed? Fooled? Scammed?

998
01:09:06,977 --> 01:09:09,229
It's way better than that.

999
01:09:11,231 --> 01:09:12,482
"An even more beat-up car"?

1000
01:09:12,566 --> 01:09:13,859
"Salvaged car"?

1001
01:09:13,942 --> 01:09:16,945
Why? You thought you were a Mercedes?

1002
01:09:18,029 --> 01:09:20,615
So, you'll show only the left side
of your face which you like,

1003
01:09:21,157 --> 01:09:23,702
eat naengmyeon that you don't like,
acting like you love it,

1004
01:09:25,745 --> 01:09:28,540
acting like you're happy
to become a princess of "Chicken Land,"

1005
01:09:28,957 --> 01:09:30,917
is that the ending you really want?

1006
01:09:31,001 --> 01:09:33,044
You called yourself genius.
You apparently aren't.

1007
01:09:33,128 --> 01:09:34,629
You said you follow your instincts.

1008
01:09:34,713 --> 01:09:38,466
You're dishonest,
not just with others, but with yourself.

1009
01:09:39,634 --> 01:09:42,387
Or you don't know what you want.

1010
01:09:45,807 --> 01:09:47,517
Do you want to say I'm pathetic?

1011
01:09:49,769 --> 01:09:51,938
Do you want to insult me
by saying I'm shallow?

1012
01:09:53,231 --> 01:09:56,026
But do you know what's really pathetic?

1013
01:09:57,694 --> 01:10:00,864
When I heard someone didn't hate me,
I thought, "Does it mean he likes me?"

1014
01:10:00,947 --> 01:10:02,282
Having that self-delusion,

1015
01:10:04,868 --> 01:10:06,912
not knowing that was just false hope.

1016
01:10:08,288 --> 01:10:09,372
Who are you talking about?

1017
01:10:09,456 --> 01:10:12,375
When you were good to me,
you were just being kind and nice.

1018
01:10:12,876 --> 01:10:14,669
When you gave me a hug, it was a free hug.

1019
01:10:14,753 --> 01:10:17,631
When you kissed me, it was... a mistake?

1020
01:10:18,548 --> 01:10:21,718
When you expressed your feelings about me,
it was an act. Right?

1021
01:10:23,887 --> 01:10:25,722
Who is the dishonest one here?

1022
01:10:25,805 --> 01:10:27,182
Was I the only one in that kiss?

1023
01:10:27,265 --> 01:10:29,684
Didn't we agree that
it was mutual and simultaneous?

1024
01:10:29,768 --> 01:10:32,145
And who said it was a mistake first?

1025
01:10:32,228 --> 01:10:35,190
Then why did you
invite me over to your place?

1026
01:10:35,273 --> 01:10:36,733
Don't you know what that implies?

1027
01:10:36,816 --> 01:10:39,611
You were feeling me out
to see if I'd say yes.

1028
01:10:39,694 --> 01:10:41,112
I didn't feel you out!

1029
01:10:41,196 --> 01:10:43,114
If not, what was it then?

1030
01:11:00,256 --> 01:11:01,633
You won't swallow your pride.

1031
01:11:01,716 --> 01:11:04,219
You can't do what embarrasses you.
Not in a million years.

1032
01:11:05,011 --> 01:11:06,054
You know what?

1033
01:11:08,014 --> 01:11:11,434
I don't have a clue
what's in that incredible heart of yours,

1034
01:11:11,518 --> 01:11:14,854
but if you can't verbalize your feelings,
don't show them in the first place.

1035
01:11:15,647 --> 01:11:18,358
Because it only makes
the one who's misled a fool.

1036
01:11:48,930 --> 01:11:50,682
TRUE TO LOVE

1037
01:11:50,765 --> 01:11:52,100
Didn't I tell you I won't do it?

1038
01:11:52,183 --> 01:11:53,935
I said I wasn't up for Deborah
from the start.

1039
01:11:54,019 --> 01:11:55,729
Hello? Is this "Kiddo?"

1040
01:11:55,812 --> 01:11:57,480
-What?
-Don't get back with him.

1041
01:11:57,564 --> 01:11:59,566
You won't remember anything anyway,
'cause you're drunk.

1042
01:11:59,649 --> 01:12:01,192
Because you love him, you marry him,

1043
01:12:01,276 --> 01:12:03,570
you're pregnant, so you have a baby,
you'll just live like that?

1044
01:12:03,653 --> 01:12:05,530
You think I'm pathetic, right?
Jin-ho doesn't.

1045
01:12:05,613 --> 01:12:06,656
He says I can do it.

1046
01:12:06,740 --> 01:12:08,992
Jin-ho, don't tell him I'm here.

1047
01:12:09,075 --> 01:12:10,618
Don't you need to go bring Yu-jeong?

1048
01:12:10,702 --> 01:12:12,662
I should figure out what to say
after I say I'm sorry.

1049
01:12:12,746 --> 01:12:15,123
If I don't get it right at once,
it gets really serious.

1050
01:12:15,206 --> 01:12:16,458
I'm sorry I'm always late.

1051
01:12:16,541 --> 01:12:19,544
Besides an apology,
don't you have anything to tell me?

1052
01:12:19,627 --> 01:12:22,172
I like you a lot, Su-hyeok.

1053
01:12:22,255 --> 01:12:23,673
And do you know what it's like now?

1054
01:12:23,757 --> 01:12:24,883
Everything is a mess.

1055
01:12:24,966 --> 01:12:26,426
Still, you have nothing to tell me?

1056
01:12:26,509 --> 01:12:29,512
Thanks for keeping your promise
that you'd let me dump you first.

1057
01:12:29,596 --> 01:12:30,638
Bo-ra.

1058
01:12:30,722 --> 01:12:31,890
Will you marry me?
